  • Combine butter and sugar
  • Add eggs one at a time
  • Add vanilla and beat well
  • Combine flour, baking powder, and salt
  • Add to batter and mix well
  • Grease and flour jelly roll pan
  • Spread all but 2 cups batter in bottom of pan
  • Spread cherry pie filling over batter then dot top of filling with reserved batter
  • Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes or until golden
  • Combine the confectioners' sugar and milk; drizzle over coffee cake. Serve warm

  • 1 cup butter, softened
  • 3/4 cup sugar
  • 4 eggs
  • 1 tsp vanilla
  • 3 cups flour
  • 1.5 tsp baking powder
  • 1/2 tsp salt
  • 1 can cherry pie filling
  • 1 cup confectioners' sugar
  • 1 to 2 tablespoons whole milk
